      "year": 2022,
      "paper": "25JulMorning",
      "question_number": 3,
      "question_text": "The depression in freezing point observed for a formic acid solution of concentration 0.5 mL L⁻¹ is 0.0405°C. Density of formic acid is 1.05 g mL⁻¹. The Van't Hoff factor of the formic acid solution is nearly: (Given for water k_f = 1.86 K kg mol⁻¹)",
      "question_type": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "topic": "Physical Chemistry - Solutions",
      "sub_topic": "Colligative properties - freezing point depression",
      "correct_answer": "C",
      "solution_summary": "[HCOOH] = 0.5 mL L⁻¹ → 0.525 g HCOOH in 1L. m = (0.525/46)/1 kg = 0.01141 mol/kg. ΔT_f = iK_fm → i = (0.0405)/(1.86×0.01141) = 1.9.",
